Author: Érico Nogueira <erico.erc@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 11 16:55:49 2021 -0300

    Revert "tui: improve support for tmux, GNU Screen"
    
    This reverts commit c266c2f36ea56220268d2b19364e28815e338c2f.
    
    This commit broke neovim under tmux, where it creates input the moment
    neovim is launched, altering the current and putting things in the
    command buffer.
    
    First is "rg", which changes the first character in the document to 'g',
    then it's ":eeee/eeee/eeee^G", which appears in the command buffer.

